<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Tadar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Hail All,<BR>   I'm looking to get my hands on an Avenger Axe (not exec axe) on the Rodcet Nife server.  If anyone know how much these sell for or if you have one for sale in the Qeynos area let me know, but I would also travel to get one.  thanks.  <P>Also, since I will be getting the Avenger Axe, I will be selling my BBC, is 75pp a good sale price for the BBC?  I don't like to haggle, I just want to get it out of my hands quickly.  thanks<P>Gravid Thornhold<BR>19th lvl Halfling Warrior<BR>Rodcet Nife</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Arek of the Nexus Knights</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><BR> On Erossi Marr the BBC sells for about 90 and the only time I've seen an avenger sold it was for 500. Hope this helps.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Ruatha</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">500pp??  Gah, somebody got rooked.<P>I've sold two of 'em.  Sold 'em for 175pp.  That's in line with what I've seen 'em offered for elsewhere.  The DMG/DLY ratio is the same as the SBH: 0.333.  And they're easier to get than the SBH if you have the time and the patience (Faldor/Placeholder is on a 90 minute spawn timer).  500pp is way more than this weapon is worth.<P>---------<BR>Ruatha Kneeslasher &lt;Wings of Honor&gt;<BR>39th Level Gnome Warriorette<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sulvar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Hmm I think that the avenger axe ratio is .3488 15 dam 43 delay so it is slightly better than the SBH.  It also has some stats, but it is not better IMO than the BBC.  I would advise you to keep your BBC and look to upgrade to a Black Iron Bastard Sword (BIBS) or a Langseax of the Wolves.<P>Also I think that you could get more for the BBC than 75pp maybe more like 100-125pp<P>------------------<BR>Gartuff Little Halfling Warrior<BR>Rarguk Orge Greenblood<BR>Azreliah Erudite Soulsucker<BR><B><A HREF="http://members.xoom.com/handofevil/" TARGET=_blank>The Hand of Evil</A></B><BR>"we're not an evil guild the name fools you"<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Ruatha</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><I>Hmm I think that the avenger axe ratio is .3488 15 dam 43 delay so it is slightly better than the SBH.</I><P>Nah.  Avenger Axe is 15/45.  I think the 15/43 axe is the Grobb Cleaver, but I'm not sure.  But the Avenger Axe is definitely 15/45.<P>---------<BR>Ruatha Kneeslasher &lt;Wings of Honor&gt;<BR>39th Level Gnome Warriorette<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sinda Ashenheart</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I've been attempting to complete this quest for nearly 3 weeks now. I have everything done except for the death of Faldor. I've sat in that room of his for 4 hours straight. I then read somewhere that there was an anti-camping code for him. I sat outside the building for another 4 hours plus and randomly checked inside (or watched for him to take his rumored walk to the gates) and nothing. I've even been told that he has to be triggered by talking to his brother in a far away zone.. So I had someone do that and waited some more.<P>Am I doing something wrong, or is he just really afraid of dwarves that look like smurfs?<P>Also, I've heard many rumors about his difficulty.. can anyone tell me how hard he'll be for a 22 warrior to take on?<P>Thank you in advance.<P>Sinda Ashenheart<BR>Love and Honor Guild of Veeshan</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sulvar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Ruatha:<BR><B><P>Nah.  Avenger Axe is 15/45.  I think the 15/43 axe is the Grobb Cleaver, but I'm not sure.  But the Avenger Axe is definitely 15/45.</B><BR><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Nope it's definately 15 dam 43 delay not 45 delay.  Check AllaKhazam's if you want   <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/biggrin.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Gartuff Little Halfling Warrior<BR>Rarguk Orge Greenblood<BR>Azreliah Erudite Soulsucker<BR><B><A HREF="http://www.handofevil.org" TARGET=_blank>The Hand of Evil</A></B><BR>"we're not an evil guild the name fools you"<p>[This message has been edited by Sulvar (edited January 31, 2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Grimdar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I've done this quest, and found that the spawn of Faldor is in fact triggered by something on the other end of the world.<P>In Dragnors Caldron is a small encampment of 4 NPCs. Most people are familiar with this camp as it is a "safe spot" to train goblins or other beasts and the NPCs dispatch them for you. Well, among the NPCs is someone with the same last name as Faldor. I forget who it is now. But if you ask that NPC "Who is Faldor" He will mention something about his "evil half brother" that hangs out in Qeynos.<P>I had a 2nd character camped at this spot to ask the question. I would then switch to my other character and 40 minutes later either "a beggar" or "Faldor" would spawn. If "a beggar" spawned I would kill him and repeat the process until Faldor spawned. Please note - there are NPC's in the Qeynos area that will KILL you if you chase Faldor too far. (including one that triple hits for 300's) Also, he would be too hard for a lvl 22 to solo I think.<P>------------------<BR>Grimdar Hillmover of Rodcet Nife<BR>50th Dwarven Warrior<BR>32nd Dwarven Paladin</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
